node.text:
Tonight @furloughfilm is having its Australian premiere at @flickerfest 
This is one of my favorite scenes/sequences from the film. I wanted to recreate the country parties we used to sometimes go to in high school. Even though we ended up cutting into it for timing, we shot the car to the party intro scene in one shot, thanks to the amazing @gclorusso_dp who jumped backwards out of the ute and followed our amazing actors @millyalcock @markella.kavenagh and @kye_lista, not to mention the AMAZING background artists who we literally poached from the local skate parks and cafes and despite most having no prior acting  experience, were so committed, patient, and collaborative. You were amazing. This party was our very first day, and it will forever be one of the best days of my life. (Albeit a sleepless, Adrenalin filled one!)
If you can make it tonight, THANKYOU! And if you can’t, I wanted to share this little clip.
Also, big massive thanks to @lotti_benardout and @haelos I sent what was basically a love letter to ask for permission to use this song in my film and it wouldn’t have worked without it. 
Spot the drinking chocolate syrup from the bottle cameo! ♥️ big love and gratitude to team furlough! Especially the one who made it a reality @jesscarrera 
Enjoy The Festival! Wish I was there x

Australians! Go see this movie! It is hands down one of the most beautiful, inspiring, raw films I’ve seen, ever. Made by two of my favorite people in the world, director @glendyn_ivin and cinematography by @samchippy, not to mention one of the most heartbreakingly honest and stunning  performances by the forever GOAT @naomiwatts and of course the incomparable #jackieweaver and @leeannawalsman 
I was lucky enough to see a screening last year, and I’ve been so excited for it to be released not only so I can watch it again but so I have other people to share my love for this film with. 
Go see it! Opens today, only IN CINEMAS!!! ♥️
@realpenguinbloom @madeupstories x

node.text:
@lafamilyhousing finds housing and provides support for thousands of unhoused people across Los Angeles. I was lucky enough to visit one of their  locations yesterday to see the kind of support they offer myself and was blown away. Join me in making welcome home baskets! 
These baskets are a really special and easy way to make moving into a temporary or permanent home as easy and comfortable as possible. A lot of those that @lafamilyhousing are supporting are entering these homes with nothing but what they have on their backs, so if you can, join me in making one of these baskets. To learn more Goto www.lafh.org/donategoods

Items to add to your welcome home baskets:
Laundry Basket
Paper towels
Toilet paper
Laundry detergent 
Utensils
Bowls and plates
Shampoo and conditioner 
Body wash
Body lotion
Kitchen tools
Pots and pans
Bath towel
Kitchen towels
Cozy blanket
Something festive!

And thanks @shelleyhennig who donated a basket too ♥️♥️

node.text:
Very grateful to be part of this panel (from afar) a night of discussions about climate change between culture leaders and climate experts. A wonderful initiative to break down and converse about environmental issues in a really candid, open way. Sometimes it’s easy to feel overwhelmed with political and scientific jargon, but this panel was a great way to share ideas and tools in a straight forward, productive way. 
Thank you for answering my question; 
“What are the most powerful actions young people can take right now to make an impact on climate change?”
You can watch the panelists thoughtful answers above. 💙 you can live stream the entire show at new-energy.co...get inspired to TAKE ACTION! x

The product I have been really loving is Skin Reset which you can learn more about on their website. 💚

node.text: Please sign the petition and share. @atyp_theatre was the catalyst for my career, a safe haven to explore and create and learn, not just how to perform, but how to tap into who I was as a young girl and to break free from my insecurities and crippling shyness. It’s so disappointing that the Australian government don’t value programs like this, @atyp_theatre is a launching pad for so many creative minds, and a safe environment for so many young people in Australia. Sign the petition, change.org/takethestage ♥️ thank you @atyp_theatre for the tools I learnt 20 years ago that I still apply to my life as an actress, and an adult navigating this world.

node.text:
Thank you @moju_music 
For sharing your words and educating myself and my followers with your thorough, thoughtful, and deeply inspiring voice.

I am honored and grateful to have shared this platform with you today through #sharethemicnowaustralia and I implore you all to keep listening and learning. 
This is a platform I am grateful to have because it allows me to connect and learn and grow with you all. 
@mojojujumusic thank you for taking the time to do this today. It was a pleasure to meet you over FaceTime last night, and to get to know more about you, and learn about your experience.

I want to close out today by sharing the incredible music video for ‘Native Tongue’ by @claudiasangiorgidalimore 
Keep amplifying and elevating BIPOC voices! 
Dancers are @djukimala 
#sharethemicnow🎤
